009,0,Status block
009,1,ACC Status,,Range:  0 ... 65535
009,2,ACC mode,Internal status),Range:  0 ... 65535
009,3,CCS status,,Range:  0 ... 65535
;
010,0,Conditions preventing the ACC from operating
010,1,,,Specification: 00000000 - ACC ready\n\nxxxxxxx1 - Bit 0 Main switch off\nxxxxxx1x - Bit 1 Minimum speed limit infringed\nxxxxx1xx - Bit 2 Brake pedal pressed\nxxxx1xxx - Bit 3 No valid gear engaged (selector lever position)\nxxx1xxxx - Bit 4 Error\nxx1xxxxx - Bit 5 External forced deactivation (e.g. electric parking brake operated. ESP status deceleration regulator. initialization or low voltage wheel speed sensors. initialization or low voltage yaw rate sender)\nx1xxxxxx - Bit 6 Vacant\n1xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Adaptive cruise control internal hardware monitoring activated
010,2,,,Specification: 00000000 - ACC ready\n\nxxxxxxx1 - Bit 0 Parking brake active\nxxxxxx1x - Bit 1 ESP cut-in (ABS ASR MSR ESP)\nxxxxx1xx - Bit 2 Minimum speed limit infringed\nxxxx1xxx - Bit 3 Brake-Only fault condition detected\nxxx1xxxx - Bit 4 External forced activation not fulfilled (e.g. increased brake temperature open circuit or short to earth in ACC sensor heater -Z47)\nxx1xxxxx - Bit 5 ACC sensor view\nx1xxxxxx - Bit 6 Invalid gearshift (manual gearbox only)\n1xxxxxxx - Bit 7 No acceleration (manual gearbox only)
010,3,,,Specification: 00000000 - ACC ready\n\nxxxxxxx1 - Bit0 Minimum engine speed infringed\nxxxxxx1x - Bit1 Minimum speed limit infringed\nxxxxx1xx - Bit 2 Forced activations not fulfilled\nxxxx1xxx - Bit 3 Forced deactivations not fulfilled\nxxx1xxxx - Bit 4 External forced activation not fulfilled (ACC deactivated via adaption channel)\nxx1xxxxx - Bit 5 Clutch open (manual gearbox only)\nx1xxxxxx - Bit 6 Hardware test not successful\n1xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Vacant
010,4,,,Specification: 00000000 - ACC ready\n\nxxxxxxx1 - Bit0 Engine speed too low (manual gearbox only)\nxxxxxx1x - Bit1 Vacant\nxxxxx1xx - Bit 2 Vacant\nxxxx1xxx - Bit 3 Vacant\nxxx1xxxx - Bit 4 Vacant\nxx1xxxxx - Bit 5 Vacant\nx1xxxxxx - Bit 6 Vacant\n1xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Vacant
;
011,0,Basic Setting
011,1,Steering Angle,Offset,
011,2,Yaw rate,Offset,
011,3,Screen for,Gong OFF,xxxxxxx0 - Bit 0 Selector lever position invalid\nxxxxxx0x - Bit 1 ACC error\nxxxxx0xx - Bit 2 Electric parking brake braking\nxxxx0xxx - Bit 3 ESP cut-in (ABS ASR MSR ESP)\nxxx0xxxx - Bit 4 Speed limit\nxx0xxxxx - Bit 5 ACC sensor view\nx0xxxxxx - Bit 6 ACC not available\n0xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Driver override prompt
011,4,Make on,GONG,xxxxxxx0 - Bit 0 Selector lever position invalid\nxxxxxx0x - Bit 1 ACC error\nxxxxx0xx - Bit 2 Electric parking brake braking\nxxxx0xxx - Bit 3 ESP cut-in (ABS ASR MSR ESP)\nxxx0xxxx - Bit 4 Speed limit\nxx0xxxxx - Bit 5 ACC sensor view\nx0xxxxxx - Bit 6 ACC not available\n0xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Driver override prompt
;
012,0,Signals from operating levers
012,1,Signals from,operating lever 1,xxxxxxx0 - Bit 0 Main switch\nxxxxxx0x - Bit 1 Abort\nxxxxx0xx - Bit 2 Reduce speed lever briefly operated\nxxxx0xxx - Bit 3 Increase speed lever tapped\nxxx0xxxx - Bit 4 Reduce speed lever pressed and held\nxx0xxxxx - Bit 5 Increase speed lever pressed and held\nx0xxxxxx - Bit 6 Fault in operating lever\n0xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Information on coding 0 = CCS 1 = ACC
012,2,Signals from,operating lever 2,xxxxxxx0 - Bit 0 Set speed\nxxxxxx0x - Bit 1 Resume speed\nxxxx00xx - Bit 2 and 3 00 = Electronic central electrics 01 = Steering wheel electronics 10 = Engine control unit (from which control unit the information is sent)\nxxx0xxxx - Bit 4 Vacant\nxx0xxxxx - Bit 5 Vacant\nx0xxxxxx - Bit 6 Distance 0 = Vacant 1 = Reduce distance slider switch pressed\n0xxxxxxx - Bit 7 Distance 0 = Vacant 1 = Increase distance slider switch pressed
